OL,3,CMinister 'sorry' to former soldier
OL,4,Cturned away from polling station over
OL,5,CID
OL,7,FThe veterans minister Johnny Mercer
OL,8,Fhas apologised to a former soldier who
OL,9,Fsays he was turned away from a polling
OL,10,Fstation because his veteran card "did
OL,11,Fnot count as proper ID".
OL,13,FFormer Army officer Adam Diver, from
OL,14,FFleetwood in Lancashire, said in a
OL,15,Fpost on X that he was "gutted" he was
OL,16,Fnot allowed to use his pass to vote in
OL,17,Fthe local elections.
OL,19,F"I'm not one for complaining but I am
OL,20,Fgutted," he said.
